<br>
I ran my Shar Vahl Taruun quests myself.  The only help I got was a nice druid who tracked an NPC for me.  I've completed every step on my own.  I've even gone back and RE-completed some of the steps when I messed up and handed in the wrong items.<br>
<br>
It did mean that I levelled more slowly.  I accepted that.  I didn't have a spoiler to follow, and I accepted that too.<br>
<br>
My wife ran her Shar Vahl Shaman quests herself.  TLC didn't stop her from completing them, although it did make them more difficult.  Again, she had to level slowly.  When we get to a point in the quests where we have to get to a higher level, we look around at the quests other NPC's are handing out in Shadeweaver's and Hollowshade, and otherwise enjoy the sheer power of the Vah Shir.<br>
